http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Prof-Raja-Angara-dead/article14025491.ece

Prof. V. Raja Angara of Department of Economics, University of Hyderabad died here on Thursday. Known as a man of theory and music, he was a known sitar player who studied at IIT-Kanpur. Within university he was known as an ardent follower of Carnatic music and an expert in economics with a focus on areas including law and economics, development economics and environmental economics. He had co-written several renowned research papers with academics and researchers from the London School of Economics. Cremation is expected to take place on Saturday.